aa(lp191
VOK, so, a quick review then, to see that you're following.
p192
aVSo the evidence that we have
p193
aVthat a quarter of the universe is dark matter \u2014
p194
aVthis gravitationally attracting stuff \u2014
p195
aVis that galaxies, the speed with which stars orbiting galaxies
p196
aVis much too large; it must be embedded in dark matter.
p197
aVThe speed with which galaxies within clusters are orbiting is much too large;
p198
aVit must be embedded in dark matter.
p199
aVAnd we see these gravitational lensing effects, these distortions
p200
aVthat say that, again, clusters are embedded in dark matter.
