aa(lp202
VOK. So now, let's turn to dark energy.
p203
aVSo to understand the evidence for dark energy, we need to discuss something
p204
aVthat Stephen Hawking referred to in the previous session.
p205
aVAnd that is the fact that space itself is expanding.
p206
aVSo if we imagine a section of our infinite universe \u2014
p207
aVand so I've put down four spiral galaxies, OK \u2014
p208
aVand imagine that you put down a set of tape measures,
p209
aVso every line on here corresponds to a tape measure,
p210
aVhorizontal or vertical, for measuring where things are.
p211
aVIf you could do this, what you would find
p212
aVthat with each passing day, each passing year,
p213
aVeach passing billions of years, OK,
p214
aVthe distance between galaxies is getting greater.
p215
aVAnd it's not because galaxies are moving
p216
aVaway from each other through space.
p217
aVThey're not necessarily moving through space.
p218
aVThey're moving away from each other
p219
aVbecause space itself is getting bigger, OK.
p220
aVThat's what the expansion of the universe or space means.
p221
aVSo they're moving further apart.
